<p>President Trump directed the Defense Department to use &quot;all available funds&quot; to ensure U.S. service members are paid on Wednesday, Oct. 15, despite the ongoing federal government shutdown [japantoday.com#1][scmp.com#1][theguardian.com#1]. He said his administration had &quot;identified funds&quot; and instructed Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth to carry out the payments, though he did not specify the funding sources or the total amount [thehindu.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. The decision guarantees pay for the military while other federal employees are expected to miss that paycheck, and it comes as Republicans have faced pressure to ensure troops are paid [csmonitor.com#1][ft.com#1]. Trump announced the directive in a Truth Social post, and some reporting noted it could remove a key pressure point on a</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/4EGtc4btt4ulpm1tRRD202IjYktjOuXV_fc3vyBfXstbYEN46nWGMJEfvwsu04baNnFucS5iLawAHt4rZnNPZV1EvyK9LMeBbKia1kwLiUDZOY7UPW26uucMWQpwqE6DFFHStweYmvRgdgV-6yQdv_NmuK2hWoJqD0FN2YD15Z1fa7E-momrbY63MQYp1P24' alt='President Trump says his administration identified funds to pay troops during the shutdown.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Funding directive: Trump ordered the Pentagon to use &quot;all available funds&quot; to pay troops during the shutdown [japantoday.com#1][scmp.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Payday timing: The directive targets the Wednesday, Oct. 15 payday to ensure service members receive their checks [csmonitor.com#1][japantoday.com#1].</li><li>Missing details: The administration did not identify the specific funding sources or the total amount to be used [thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Chain of command: Trump instructed Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth to execute the payments [straitstimes.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Political context: Republicans were under pressure to ensure troops receive pay as the shutdown continues [ft.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>I am using my authority, as commander-in-chief, to direct our secretary of war, Pete Hegseth, to use all available funds to get our troops PAID on October 15. - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: Framed the move as using commander-in-chief authority to ensure troops are paid on Oct. 15 despite the shutdown. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/oct/11/trump-shutdown-military-pay'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Republican lawmakers: Faced pressure to issue paychecks to U.S. forces as the congressional standoff drags on. (<a href='https://www.ft.com/content/3780f953-b052-406c-b726-0a4b17acc95d'>Financial Times</a>)</li><li>Congressional negotiators: With troop pay protected, one pressure point on Congress to resolve the shutdown could be reduced. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3328666/trump-orders-pentagon-use-all-available-funds-pay-troops-despite-shutdown'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/trump-says-his-administration-identified-funds-to-pay-troops-during-shutdown/article70153232.ece'>Trump says his administration &#x27;identified funds&#x27; to pay troops during shutdown</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/trump-directs-the-pentagon-to-use-%27all-available-funds%27-to-ensure-troops-are-paid-despite-shutdown'>Trump directs Pentagon to use &#x27;all available funds&#x27; to ensure troops are paid despite shutdown</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/trump-says-his-administration-identified-funds-to-pay-us-troops-during-shutdown'>Trump says his administration ‘identified funds’ to pay US troops during shutdown</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/3780f953-b052-406c-b726-0a4b17acc95d'>Trump says military will be paid during US government shutdown</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2025/1011/governm